dataIdInfo.idPurp: As part of the community data layers, the high school districts boundary map layer is an integral part of the Fayette County Public Schools (FCPS) districting analysis. Community data layers are accessed by personnel in most FCPS analysts for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production. More advanced user applications may focus on thematic mapping, summarization of data by geography, or planning purposes (including defining boundaries, managing assets and facilities, integrating attribute databases with geographic features, spatial analysis, and presentation output).
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset represents the boundaries for high school districts as defined by Fayette County Public Schools. The districts define attendance for each of the public high schools in Fayette County and are digitized by FCPS staff utilizing base map information.
